        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 7:23PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 722 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Collierville, moving northeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cayce, Yum Yum, Stanton, Belmont, Oakland, Kirk, Rossville,
Arlington, Brunswick, Fisherville, Laconia, Collierville, Macon,
Fairhaven, Canadaville, Keeling, Williston, Lambert, Gainesville, and
Mason.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for northwestern
Mississippi...and west Tennessee.</instruction>
